<TEXT>
hundreds of local law enforcement 
officers were buying and selling cocaine friday in sting operations 
across the state aimed at slowing down streetlevel drug traffic 
operation rock pile made at least 480 arrests friday during its 
first night 
to our knowledge its the first time anything like this has 
been done george crolius a broward county sheriffs spokesman 
said in a telephone interview from the fort lauderdale command 
center 
the florida sheriffs association organized the operation john 
doyle an assistant project director with the national sheriffs 
association in alexandria va said he had never heard of local law 
enforcement agencies working together in a statewide effort 
although other states have had statewide operations organized from a 
state level 
fifteen city police departments and at least 61 of floridas 66 
sheriffs departments are participating according to crolius who 
estimated that more than 1000 officers were involved in the project 
dade county which has a countywide police department rather than 
a sheriffs office is also participating 
the crackdown was scheduled to end midnight saturday 
the operation is targeted equally at buyers and sellers and 
includes both buy busts which result in the arrests of dealers 
and reverse stings which result in the arrests of users search 
warrants will be served as well 
most arrests will probably be made in urban areas like broward 
and dade counties the orlando area and tampa and st petersburg 
crolius said 
</TEXT>
