police swarmed through ganginfested 
neighborhoods friday night in the first widespread dragnet for 
drugdealing street thugs since the highlypublicized sweeps dubbed 
the hammer last summer 
the eighthour operation on the eve of the july fourth holiday 
weekend targeted gangs in the three neighborhoods terrorized by 
gangs 
assistant chief robert vernon told 300 officers at a 4 pm roll 
call that they should remember many residents are lawabiding 
citizens 
portable booking trailers were set up at the police departments 
southeast division station in the heart of the watts district which 
was ravaged by riots in 1965 
police made 70 arrests in the first four hours of the operation 
30 of them narcotics felonies and 19 of those arrested were 
identified as gang members said police detective tony celli twenty 
vehicles lacking current registration tags were impounded he said 
we are here to enforce all the laws that are applicable said 
celli 
community outcry over gang thugs who keep residents prisoners in 
their own homes prompted the first fullscale police assault in 
april 1988 the 1000officer weekend sweeps continued at intervals 
through the summer 
mayor tom bradley a former police lieutenant sworn to a fifth 
term friday vowed during the first of the 1000officer gang task 
force sweeps 15 months ago we are going to take these terrorists 
off the streets of los angeles 
gang violence continued unabated 
more than one person died in a county gangrelated killing for 
every day of 1988 there were 452 gangrelated slayings in los 
angeles county in 1988 surpassing the 387 gangrelated murders 
reported the year before 
