baroness gaitskell widow of former labor party 
leader hugh gaitskell died today in her sleep at home in london 
she was 88 
lady gaitskell who preferred being called dora was born in 
russia but her parents moved the family to london in 1903 
she joined the labor party at 16 met gaitskell at a byelection 
campaign in 1929 and married him in 1937 after divorcing her first 
husband 
he was elected labor party leader in 1955 and died in 1963 
dora gaitskell was one of those political wives who really 
emerged as a political figure in her own right but who provided 
essential support and inspiration to her husband said denis 
healey a labor party lawmaker 
lady gaitskell was made a life peer in 1963 and was known in the 
house of lords as a champion of human rights reform of the law on 
homosexuality and aid to developing countries 
she was britains delegate to the human rights committee at the 
united nations for four years in the 1960s and received honorary 
degrees from the universities of manchester and leeds 
she is survived by two daughters by gaitskell and a son by her 
first marriage 
