the second collect at evensong 
o god from whom all holy desires all good counsels and all 
just works do proceed give unto thy servants that peace which the 
world cannot give that both our hearts may be set to obey thy 
commandments and also that by thee we being defended from the fear 
of our enemies may pass our time in rest and quietness through the 
merits of jesus christ our saviour amen 
