<TEXT>
a tanker carrying badly needed fuel broke 
through syrias blockade of the christian enclave sparking a fierce 
artillery duel that killed three people and wounded 16 police said 
saturday 
iraq syrias main arab rival said it was ready to cut off vital 
arms supplies to the christians to help arab league peace efforts 
there was no immediate reaction from christian leader gen michel 
aoun the army commander and head of a christian cabinet vying with 
a moslem cabinet to lead the government 
the official iraqi news agency in baghdad quoted a foreign 
ministry spokesman as warning the syrians not to take advantage 
of the iraqi move or commit any aggression against other parties 
in lebanon 
there was no immediate comment from syria 
the christians have relied heavily on the iraqi arms shipments 
including t54 tanks and multibarreled rocket launchers in their 
confrontation with the syrians and their moslem militia allies 
the arab league so far has failed to halt the fighting which 
began march 8 
the syrians and their allies imposed the land and sea blockade on 
the 310squaremile christian enclave on march 14 the blockade has 
caused a serious shortage of gasoline and oil and has turned the 
oncebustling area into a ghost town 
aouns cabinet has been buying gasoline abroad and shipping it to 
the christian enclave in small tankers syrian artillery pounds the 
christian coastline daily to stop the ships and one was hit and set 
ablaze a few weeks ago 
police declined to say how much fuel was aboard the ship that 
made it through saturday 
a christian source speaking on condition of anonymity said the 
small tanker ventured through syrian shellfire friday night to 
anchor in a small bay about 15 miles north of beirut 
he said the tanker unloaded its cargo of gasoline and sailed out 
before dawn saturday he declined to identify the ship 
the syrians opened fire at the departing tanker aouns gunners 
fired back to provide the ship with cover the ship made it through 
the blockade and headed to cyprus but the exchange escalated and 
spread the source said 
a spokesman for aoun refused to comment on the fighting 
the casualties brought to 385 the number of people killed since 
the fighting began in march 1515 have been wounded 
a police spokesman said syrian forces were firing six shells and 
rockets a minute for some periods before dawn 
the barrage hit the ashrafiyeh and ein rummaneh districts of 
christian east beirut the coastline north of the capital and wooded 
valleys east of the waterfront where aouns artillery batteries are 
deployed the spokesman said 
he said aouns gunners retaliated with 155mm howitzer fire on 
syrian artillery emplacements along west beiruts seaside boulevard 
and the mountains overlooking the city 
the spokesman said the christian gunners scored several direct 
hits on syrian artillery emplacements in west beirut 
witnesses speaking on condition of anonymity reported seeing a 
syrian army ambulance rushing to scene shortly before dawn 
syrian headquarters in beirut refused comment 
as the firing intensified around daybreak families rushed for 
cover in underground shelters and basements 
the barrage eased about 8 am and police said hundreds of 
families left west beirut for safer areas in southern lebanon and 
the bekaa valley in eastern lebanon 
police said a similar evacuation was reported in east beirut 
with christians headed for the mountains northeast of the city 
