signed an agreement saturday to cooperate on environmental 
protection the state news agency pap reported 
under the agreement the countries are to set up constant 
monitoring of air pollution a tripartite government commission will 
be established to supervise implementation of the agreement it said 
the agreement contains commitments to prevent further 
degradation of the natural environment particularly in border 
regions the agency said 
prime ministers mieczyslaw f rakowski of poland ladislav adamec 
of czechoslovakia and willi stoph chairman of the east german 
council of ministers met in the southwestern city of wroclaw for the 
