the governments are concerned about the noxious effects on the 
environment of sulphur dioxide and phosphorous oxides the agency 
said 
rakowski was quoted as saying degradation of the environment 
in southwestern poland water soil and air pollution has reached a 
catastrophic state a real threat has surfaced of the ecological 
balance being tipped and the region turning into a desert 
the smell of burning brown coal used for fuel hangs heavy over a 
number of cities in the region including the industrial center of 
katowice one of the most polluted cities in poland even clear days 
are often hazy from industrial pollution 
