manufacturing in chinas northern provinces is more likely to be 
affected by political unrest than factories elsewhere in the country 
this is because most of the turmoil seems to have flared up 
around chinas economically developed areas and educational centers 
he says 
potential production snarls wont hit all types of fireworks 
factories assembling firecrackers a highly laborintensive task 
mainly are located in the more rural part of chinas southern 
provinces so firecracker shipments arent likely to be disrupted 
says trout 
adding to problems that might arise from developments on the 
political front trout says hes been informed that several chinese 
factories are facing financial trouble 
a lack of credit to cover material and other costs has put three 
or four factories in hunan province in danger of closing the 
southeastern province annually accounts for about 15 percent of 
chinas total fireworks shipments to the united states which came 
to more than 50 million pounds in 1987 the most recent year for 
which us government figures were available 
