some provinces both from a political standpoint and a financial 
standpoint says trout 
people in the fireworks business say there are only a few 
countries that could help fill a potential shortfall in chinese 
shipments and there are limits to how much places such as hong 
kong taiwan and macao the portugueseadministered territory off 
chinas southeastern coast could compensate 
conkling of the pyrotechnics trade group says fireworks are an 
important export for china 
the country was becoming a powerful force in fireworks just 
before former president richard nixon reopened trade with the 
country in the early 1970s it has come to dominate the industry 
today largely because its factories turn out products of acceptable 
quality at unbeatable prices due to low labor costs 
fireworks is a legitmate science in china universities do 
research into pyrotechnics and fireworks and this translates into 
big business for the country says conkling 
for years china has kept fireworks prices down very close to 
the cost of production to attract customers but us businesses 
say that even before the political problems they were told to expect 
price hikes of 15 percent to 30 percent for next seasons orders as 
the chinese try to eke out more profit 
us retail sales of fireworks will total about 200 million this 
year the industry says 
government figures indicate china supplies about 76 percent by 
weight of all fireworks brought into the united states but the 
industry says the figures probably understate chinese imports 
as chinas shipments have grown the quality has been slipping 
possibly because newer factories arent as familiar with us 
regulations all imported fireworks must meet the same safety 
standards as domestically made products 
trout who also is president of the industrys trade association 
